@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "X_marks" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game board consists of an 8 by 8 tiles area where empty tiles
are displayed. Numbers appear at the right of the game board, as
well as on the lower row under the game board. Those numbers
indicate, by their respective position, how many crosses are on
each row or column. Obviously, if there is a zero on a column or
row, then there are no crosses on the associated column or row of
tiles.

  Gameplay is pretty simple: just click on a tile you suspect that
might contain a cross. If a cross is there, it will be exposed,
otherwise, that tile will return to its normal state.

  At the lower right of the game board is an 'X' icon indicating
the number of crosses found as well as the total number of crosses
you have to find on the game board.

  The main goal is to find all crosses using the least amount of
moves...

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button. To quit, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

